<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/graphics15/BeltoftheGreatTurtle.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
And 2 items for small quests that give:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/graphics15/lodizalshellshield.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/graphics15/eyepatch_of_plunder.JPG"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Seven; would we need resist gear, underwater gear, or other special equipment?<br>
Nope, he's pure melee.. so bring your AC <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Eight; How many do you think we need? 12 or 18, 54th plus?<br>
Around 12 to 18, depending on balance of who we have, would want mostly melee and healers I'm assuming<br>
<br>
Nine; what basic tactic would we use?<br>
Dunno... I'm thinking if he's slowable would tash, then highest malo line, then chaincast slow (Many a dead enc/shm during this time :P), no idea if there's something better.<br>
If he isn't, highest tank goes in and builds aggro for 15 seconds or so, and then everyone else runs in, attacking him in the back to avoid riposte ane enrage.<br>
Or could get the little turtle to tank him, and then start switching aggro over when the little guy is down to 25% or so.<br>
These are just tactics off the top of my head, probably much better out there.<br>
